  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide quality community management of acute malnutrition services, strengthen capacity building and nutrition surveillance in Pigi, Fangak, Akobo (Jonglei) and Leer (Unity) counties.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will strive to offer high impact and life-saving nutrition interventions targeting children below five years and PLWs of host communities, IDPs and other vulnerable populations in Fangak, Pigi, Akobo and Leer. The project will have a strong component of community mobilization to enhance active case finding through the screening of PLWs and the under fives and support the necessary referral linkages to the facility/program to ensure treatment of SAM and MAM cases. In the nutrition centres, the nutrition staff will take anthropometric measurements either MUAC or weight and height) and enrol/admit children screened with SAM into the OTP program and receive a week&#x2019;s ration of RUTF, children screened with MAM will be admitted to the TSFP and receive a two weeks ration of RUSF, the green MUAC/median will be educated on good nutrition practices to maintain and/or improve the nutrition status of the children.</narrative>
  </description>
